<subsection component="1031">
  <title>Derivatives</title>
  
  <assemblage>
    <title>Derivatives 1</title>
    <p>
      I can compute the derivative of a function using the limit definition.
    </p>
  </assemblage>

  <assemblage>
    <title>Derivatives 2</title>
    <p>
      I can compute the derivative of a function using
      <ul>
	<li>
	  <p>the power rule,</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	  <p>the sum/difference rule, and</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	  <p>the constant multiple rule.</p>
	</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </assemblage>

  <assemblage>
    <title>Derivatives 3</title>
    <p>
      I can compute the derivative of a product of two or more functions.
    </p>
  </assemblage>


  <assemblage>
    <title>Derivatives 4</title>
    <p>
      I can compute the derivative of a composition of two or more functions.
    </p>
  </assemblage>

  <assemblage>
    <title>Derivatives 3</title>
    <p>
      I can use implicit differentiation to solve related rates problems.
    </p>
  </assemblage>
</subsection>
